---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { buttonVariants } from "@/components/ui/button";
import VisualEditor from "@/components/VisualEditor.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Rust vs C/C++ - A Comprehensive Comparison"
  description="Compare Rust and C/C++ across memory safety, performance, developer productivity, and more."
>
  <div class="container py-10">
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight font-display">
        Rust vs C/C++: A Comprehensive Comparison
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-muted-foreground font-body">
        Understanding the strengths and tradeoffs of modern systems programming languages
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none font-body">
      <p>This page contains a detailed comparison between Rust and C/C++, focusing on memory safety, performance characteristics, developer productivity, and interoperability.</p>
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-display mt-8">Memory Safety</h2>
      
      <p>Rust's ownership system provides memory safety guarantees at compile time without garbage collection overhead, preventing common issues like buffer overflows, use-after-free vulnerabilities, and data races.</p>
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-display mt-8">Performance</h2>
      
      <p>Both languages offer similar performance characteristics, with Rust providing safety guarantees without significant overhead. Benchmark results show Rust consistently performs within 0-5% of optimized C++ code.</p>
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-display mt-8">Developer Experience</h2>
      
      <p>Rust provides modern developer tooling including Cargo for package management, clear compiler error messages, built-in documentation, and a first-party testing framework.</p>
      
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-display mt-8">Interoperability</h2>
      
      <p>Both languages can work together in the same codebase, allowing for incremental migration from C/C++ to Rust.</p>
      
      <div class="mt-8 flex justify-center">
        <a href="/" class={buttonVariants({ size: "lg" })}>
          Return to Home
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- DO NOT REMOVE - Necessary for making visual edits via new.website! -->
  <VisualEditor />
</BaseLayout>